"```sql\nSELECT e.expense_description, SUM(e.cost) AS total_value\nFROM expense e\nJOIN event ev ON e.link_to_event = ev.event_id\nWHERE ev.event_name = 'October Meeting' AND e.approved = 'true'\nGROUP BY e.expense_description;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the type of expenses (`expense_description`) and their total approved value (`SUM(cost)`) for the event named 'October Meeting'. It joins the `expense` table with the `event` table using the foreign key relationship and filters for approved expenses."